4.2.	What Media Should Be Used?

A significant portion of the documentation will be in the form of hard copy documents. These would include procedures manuals, charts or maps, reference books and other similar records. As previously noted, some facilities utilize computer modeling systems to monitor and/or predict the dispersion of toxic or flammable releases. These systems can be used to manage data such as:

•	a list of substances that are held on-site and that can be modeled;
•	physical and toxicological properties of these substances;
•	local meteorological data (based on historical records and/or real-time input); and
•	map of the facility and surrounding regions (including key buildings and roadways, population distributions, etc.).

