Dissemination of Results. The organizations' PSM program documentation should address who will receive the audit reports. Since the audit is a report to management on the effectiveness of one or more facility PSM elements, the report would typically be addressed to the responsible site manager, who will have overall responsibility, and to appropriate members of the organization's management. Other copies, or as a minimum, relevant extracts, should be provided to each person who is assigned responsibility for resolution of recommendations contained in the report.

3.3.	Resolution of Audit Recommendations

It is common, because of an audit, to formulate recommendations (e.g., to correct documentation deficiency identified during the audit). It is important to promptly and fully resolve each recommendation. A discussion of documentation of recommendations and their resolution should be made. The resolution of recommendations may be documented within the audit report itself, within an addendum to the report, or in a separate follow-up report issued later.

4.	Records Management

The organization's PSM program documentation should define pertinent audit program records management practices.

4.1.	Storage Locations

Audit records should be accessible to those parties responsible for implementing PSM within a facility or organization, especially those charged with the responsibility for resolving audit findings or recommendations. Additionally, organizations may find it helpful to have a centralized compilation of audit records to facilitate trend analysis or to a

